title: I-35E Dallas photos

pageHeader.title: Roadside Views North of Dallas
pageHeader.lastUpdated: Dec 19, 2021 ($655 million expansion started); Apr 18, 2023 (remove archive photos)

text: The phase 1 expansion of IH-35E from LBJ Freeway to Lake Lewisville was completed in 2017. Work on the $655 million second phase between IH 635 and the Bush Turnpike began in 2022. Work at the Main Street intersection in Lewisville began in 2023.

images.caption: Looking southbound along the frontage road at the Bush Turnpike Interchange.

Looking southbound along the frontage road, with the Bush Turnpike Interchange ahead.
Looking northwest (northbound) from the Frankford overpass, showing the collector-distributor lanes and two-lane reversible HOT facility which both were completed in 2017.
Looking west at the ramps at the massive interchange at SH 121 (Rayburn Turnpike). This interchange was fully opened to traffic in 2018.
Looking west along the SH 121 frontage road.
